The paper deals with image segmentation of historical documents using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) for weight initialization is a statistical technique, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method compared to state-of-the-art techniques, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) and deep learning (cs.DL).
